<h1>For BYUI Parents</h1>
<p>Sending your son or daugther to college can be an exciting yet challenging time for you as a parent. We understand the importance of receiving timley and essential information you need to make this a good experience for both you and your daughter/son. The purpose of this site is to help you connect to the resources you need, stay informed, and better understand the spirit and mission of BYU-Idaho.</p>
<p>Here are some links to information you might be interested in:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<h2><a href="x28865.xml">Get Connected (Orientation)</a></h2>
<div id="info">Parents of new students are invited to participate in Get                     Connected during the Move-in Day (the first day of Get Connected)                      prior to the start of school.<br /><br />We realize that not all parents are able to travel to Rexburg with their student.                     We are planning on streaming the BYU-Idaho Welcome with President and Sister                     Clark over the internet. Check back here for the link.</div>
</li>
<li>
<h2><a href="x43420.xml">Stay Connected</a></h2>
Sign up to receive text notifications and the parents' version of the  new student update which is e-mailed on a weekly basis from our office  to all admitted students who have accepted their offer. </li>
<li>
<h2><a href="#">Admitted Student Checklist</a></h2>
We have a specialized checklist for every starting semester and student admissions type which was created to help guide you in your preparations to start school.</li>
<li>
<h2><a href="#">Important Deadlines</a></h2>
These are some important and fun things happening in the next few months! </li>
<li>
<h2><a href="x30305.xml">Student Ambassadors</a></h2>
Every admitted student is assigned a Student Ambassador,                       volunteers who help your son or daughter with any  questions they may have. </li>
<br /> 
</ul>
